        <section>
            <title>General</title>

            <table class="general">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <tbody>

                        
                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="ttps://github.com/emory-libraries/eulexistdb">EULexistdb</ulink></td>
                            <td>EULexistdb is a Python module that provides utilities and classes for interacting with 
                                the eXist-db XML Database (version 1.4) in a pythonic, object-oriented way, with optional Django integration.</td>
                        </tr>     
                        
                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="http://code.google.com/p/existdb-contrib/">eXist-db contrib</ulink></td>
                            <td>eXist-db contrib is a collection of tools, module, functions, extensions, etc. for eXist-db, hosted by google code - a
                                "playground for code that might be integrated with the eXist database in the future".</td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="http://fluent.exist-db.org/">Fluent</ulink></td>
                            <td>Piotr Kaminski contributed an extension package org.exist.fluent, an API for databases running in embedded mode that takes
                                advantage of Java 5.0 features.</td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="https://github.com/knipknap/pyexist">PYexist</ulink></td>
                            <td>A simple Python library for communicating with an eXist XML database via its REST API</td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="https://github.com/fsteeg/sinist">Sinist</ulink></td>
                            <td>A simple (and very early) Scala wrapper to access eXist DB</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="http://www.xqjapi.com/exist/">XQJ API</ulink></td>
                            <td>A very fast XQJ API implementation for eXist-db, released by Charles Foster.</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="http://www.xmlsh.org/ModuleExist">xmlsh - XML Shell</ulink></td>
                            <td>An extension for connecting to exist-db from xmlsh, the command line shell for XML released by David A. Lee.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="doclink"><ulink url="http://montag.sourceforge.net/docs/configuration.html">Montag - Web Services middleware</ulink></td>
                            <td>Montag aims to provide Web Services for any XML:DB API enabled database, and has support for eXist-db.</td>
                        </tr>

                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>

        </section>

